Always read these files before generating or evaluating any code in this repo:

1. .agent.md — artifact list, canonical paths, industrial checklist
2. docs/CODE_TEMPLATE.md — mandatory structure for all CODE.md files (lean format, DSA diagram guide)
3. docs/AI_EVAL_FRAMEWORK.md — AI-based evaluation protocol (replaces pytest)
4. docs/EVALUATION_RUBRIC.md — gates G1–G7, dimension weights D1–D7, scoring 0–100

Key rules:
- Generate exactly 5 files per day: CODE.md, code.py, EXERCISE.md, ex01–ex03 stubs.
- NO EVALUATION.md (scoring lives in EXERCISE.md).
- NO test_exercises.py (evaluation is AI-based per docs/AI_EVAL_FRAMEWORK.md).
- CODE.md must follow docs/CODE_TEMPLATE.md (≤80 lines, concepts table, pitfalls).
- DSA CODE.md must include a Visual/Diagram section (ASCII or Mermaid) per the diagram guide in docs/CODE_TEMPLATE.md.
- Exercise stubs must have inline assert checks in __main__ (not pytest).
- EXERCISE.md must include a "Suggested Practice" section with 1–2 external links.
